Knicks Beat Heat 72-70
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Just when it looked like the New York Knicks were dead, they
reached deep down and summoned a dramatic comeback from an 18-point deficit to
send their series against Miami to a winner-take-all finale for the fourth
straight year. Overcoming Miami's relentless defense and their own self-doubts
after a miserable first half, the Knicks rallied past Miami 72-70 tonight to
force a deciding Game 7 on Sunday. It was an incredible comeback given the way
the Heat dominated for most of the game, but the Knicks -- like they did last
year in their improbable run to the finals -- found a way to thrive on adversity
and save their playoff lives.
</P>
