<HEADLINE> Philly To Press On With Development  </HEADLINE>
By MICHAEL RUBINKAM
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The deadly collapse of a wooden pier will
not affect plans for a $190 million entertainment and retail
complex on the Philadelphia waterfront, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   After years of delay, construction at Penn's Landing, which is
within walking distance of the pier that collapsed Thursday night,
is set to begin in August or September. Opening is slated for fall
2002.
