<HEADLINE> Gunshot Critically Injures La. Girl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- A game of cops and robbers with a real
handgun nearly killed a 7-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
   Her 8-year-old brother found the handgun on top of a VCR while
the children were alone after school Friday, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The TEC-9 semiautomatic pistol was loaded with a 30-round clip.
One bullet fired during the game, and hit the girl in the side,
Officer Stacey Adams said. The boy ran across the street and told a
neighbor.
</P>
<P>
   The girl remained in critical condition Saturday at Louisiana
State University hospital. Neither child's name was released.
</P>
<P>
   Adams said their mother's boyfriend picked them up from school
and asked a neighbor to watch them while he paid a bill.
</P>
<P>
   It was unclear how long the boyfriend was gone. Police arrested
him outside the house on misdemeanor marijuana possession. A felony
charge of second-degree cruelty to a juvenile later was added.
</P>
<P>
   The boy will not be charged because the shooting was accidental
and because of his age, Sgt. Jimmy Muller said.
</P>
