<SUBHEAD>
Nine Aspiring NATO Members To Ally
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   VILNIUS, Lithuania (AP) -- Nine aspiring NATO members urged the Western
defense alliance to invite them to join by 2002 and agreed to work together to
ensure that happens. A joint statement adopted Friday at the end of a conference
on the North Atlantic Treaty Organization's role in European security called on
the alliance to invite the nine countries to join at the next summit two years
