<HEADLINE> Abby Girl Wins Railbird Stakes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Abby Girl overtook 7-5 favorite Cover
Gal in the final strides to win Saturday's $150,000 Railbird Stakes
at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Golden Ballet earned her first career victory by beating Shine
Up Ciel by a half-length in the $92,775 Nursery Stakes.
</P>
<P>
   Abby Girl, ridden by Corey Nakatani and carrying 119 pounds,
covered seven furlongs in 1:22 2-5 and, as the 8-5 second-favorite,
paid $5.20, $2.60 and $2.20.
</P>
<P>
   Abby Girl's second straight stakes victory and fourth win in
seven lifetime starts was worth $90,000, raising the Kentucky-bred
daughter of Meadowlake's career earnings to $298,170.
</P>
<P>
   Cover Gal, ridden by Laffit Pincay Jr. and carrying 122 pounds,
crossed the finish line two lengths in front of Wired To Fly and
returned $2.60 and $2.20.
</P>
<P>
   Wired To Fly, ridden by Joe Bravo and carrying 122 pounds, was
four lengths ahead of Classic Olympio at the wire and paid $2.40 to
show. Miss Pixie was fifth and last in the 38th running of the race
for 3-year-old fillies.
</P>
<P>
   Golden Ballet, ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye and carrying 116
pounds, covered 4{ furlongs in 51 seconds in winning the 32nd
running of the Nursery Stakes for 2-year-old fillies, and paid
$20.20, $7.40 and $4.60.
</P>
<P>
   Golden Ballet lost to Shine Up Ciel by two lengths in her
previous start.
</P>
<P>
   Kisbey, the 2-1 favorite ridden by Nakatani, finished seventh.
</P>
