<HEADLINE> 'Friends' Actor in Car Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Actor Matthew Perry wrecked his Porsche
Saturday when he swerved to avoid a car on the narrow streets of
the Hollywood Hills and drove into someone's porch, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The 30-year-old star of the hit TV show ''Friends'' was
uninjured, said Sgt. Paul Partridge. Perry was not under the
influence or drugs or alcohol at the time of the noon accident,
Partridge said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mr. Perry was driving downhill, and he swerved to avoid
another vehicle, probably coming the other direction. He wasn't
able to regain control and ran off the road,'' Partridge said.
</P>
<P>
   Perry's green Porsche was damaged and had to be towed, Partridge
said.
</P>
<P>
   He said no police report was made because nobody was hurt and
there was no evidence of wrongdoing. Officers helped Perry and the
residents exchange phone numbers and insurance information.
</P>
<P>
   Perry is one of six co-stars of the wildly popular ''Friends,''
a staple of NBC's Thursday night lineup. In a deal reached earlier
this month, Perry and the other actors will be paid $750,000 per
episode for two years.
</P>
</TEXT>
