<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bayern Munich Wins Bundesliga Title  </HEADLINE>
By NESHA STARCEVIC
<TEXT>
<P>
   HAMBURG, Germany (AP) -- Bayern Munich completed an improbable
double and won the Bundesliga title Saturday when it beat Werder
Bremen 3-1 and Bayer Leverkusen lost 2-0 at Unterhaching.
</P>
<P>
   Leverkusen went into the final round with a three-point lead and
needed only a draw in Unterhaching to clinch its first title. But
it allowed an early own goal and gave up another goal in the second
half, then wasted several great opportunities and ended up
empty-handed.
</P>
<P>
   Not far away, in Munich's sold-out Olympic Stadium, Bayern
romped over Bremen on two early goals by striker Carsten Jancker to
celebrate its 16th Bundesliga title, a record.
</P>
<P>
   Bayern also won the German Cup two weeks ago, but was knocked
out of the Champions League semifinals by Real Madrid.
</P>
<P>
   ''We played a great season and attractive soccer,'' Leverkusen
coach Christoph Daum said. ''Today, we didn't use our best
opportunities. We are deeply sad, it's a huge disappointment.''
</P>
<P>
   Both teams finished with 73 points, but Bayern retained the
title on better goal differential.
</P>
<P>
   ''I feel sorry for Daum. All my compliments to Unterhaching,''
said Bayern coach Ottmar Hitzfeld. ''Leverkusen would have deserved
it, too. It was one of the toughest title fights Bayern has had.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
