<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Petter Villegas scored in the sixth
minute of overtime to give the New York-New Jersey MetroStars a 3-2
victory over the Tampa Bay Mutiny on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Adolfo Valencia scored in the 58th and 88th minutes as the
MetroStars (4-6-0) rallied from a 2-0 deficit.
