<HEADLINE> Revolution 1, Fire 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Wolde Harris scored his fourth goal in as many
games and the New England shut down the Chicago Fire's strong
attack in the Revolution's 1-0 victory Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago (5-5-1) led the league in scoring after its four goals
against San Jose a week ago and had plenty of chances Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Forward Ante Razov twice missed tying goals by inches. In the
